It seems that I forgot to include the opening `<` tags for some of the elements.

Here is the corrected XML mission plan:
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Mission xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://robust-mission-planning.com/mission.xsd
         http://robust-mission-planning.com/mission.xsd">
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <DrivingToTree location="${tree1}" />
    <TakePicture action="picture" />
    <If condition="${pictureLowTemperature}">
      <TakeTemperatureReading />
      <If condition="${temperatureLow}">
        <TakeCO2Sample />
        <DriveToFarAwayTree location="${farawayTree}" />
        <RepeatTaskDescription>
          <DrivingToTree location="${tree1}" />
          <TakePicture action="picture" />
          <If condition="${pictureLowTemperature}">
            <TakeTemperatureReading />
            <If condition="${temperatureLow}">
              <TakeCO2Sample />
              <DriveToFarAwayTree location="${farawayTree}" />
              <!-- repeat indefinitely -->
            </If>
          </If>
        </RepeatTaskDescription>
      </If>
    </If>
    <If condition="${!pictureLowTemperature}">
      <DrivingToEnd location="${end}" />
    </If>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>
</Mission>
```
I added the opening `<` tags for `DrivingToTree`, `TakePicture`, and `RepeatTaskDescription`. This should resolve the error.

Please note that I also removed the extra `TaskDescription` element, as it was not necessary. Let me know if you have any further issues!